<span id="freeTextContainer11019255067860394560">Worth it for the poems from North alone. Scary good. Heaney is a masterful poet of ambivalence and ambiguity, two themes that he often reflects on as he navigates irish politics and attempts to reconcile the Ireland of old with modernity. I feel like I&apos;ve discovered an honest to god treasure in this book. Beautiful beautiful poetry </span>
